../../fix-report.md:76:1. **EIP-2935 history state non-mainnet constants + invalid fork backfill** (`packages/vm/src/actions/accumulateParentBlockHash.ts`) — fixed in H02
../../fix-report.md:147:All seven reviewed findings were verified as real and addressed with narrow changes inside `packages/vm`. The fixes keep block execution state changes within one checkpoint, restore temporary state-root and hardfork changes on failure, and align builder behavior with runner/consensus expectations. No findings were deferred or skipped.
../../fix-report.md:151:### [CRITICAL] EIP-2935 history state is written with non-mainnet constants and an invalid fork backfill
../../fix-report.md:154:**Issue:** The helper wrote EIP-2935 history to the wrong address/window and backfilled pre-fork ancestors.
../../fix-report.md:155:**Fix:** Switched to canonical mainnet defaults with Common-param lookup where available, used an 8191-slot ring, and removed fork-block ancestor backfill.
../../fix-report.md:157:### [HIGH] `runBlock` exposes `setHardfork` but never applies it to the VM/EVM execution context
../../fix-report.md:160:**Issue:** `setHardfork` was documented but ignored, so execution used the VM's existing hardfork.
../../fix-report.md:161:**Fix:** Added temporary hardfork selection by block number/timestamp, aligned VM/EVM/block Common instances for execution, and restored prior hardforks in `finally`.
../../fix-report.md:169:### [HIGH] DAO fork balance moves are committed even when the block fails
../../fix-report.md:173:**Fix:** Moved DAO fork application inside the same checkpoint that wraps block execution and validation.
../../fix-report.md:181:### [MEDIUM] Block execution disables tx/block hardfork validation by default
../../fix-report.md:184:**Issue:** `runBlock` transaction application defaulted to skipping hardfork validation.
../../fix-report.md:210:All seven reviewed findings were verified as real and addressed with scoped changes under `packages/state`. The fixes tighten state consistency around storage cache clearing, account deletion, canonical dumps, forked missing-account detection, root loading, storage-range pagination, and fork proof block pinning. No findings were deferred or treated as false positives.
../../fix-report.md:250:### [MEDIUM] `getProof` can read a different fork block than cached state
../../fix-report.md:253:**Issue:** Fork proofs used the current fork block tag without first resolving and pinning it.
../../fix-report.md:263:<summary><strong>H04 — Blockchain + receipts + persistence</strong></summary>
../../fix-report.md:265:# Blockchain + receipts + persistence fix report
../../fix-report.md:269:**Scope:** packages/blockchain packages/receipt-manager packages/sync-storage-persister
../../fix-report.md:273:All seven findings were verified as real and addressed with scoped changes. The fixes tighten deletion invariants in the blockchain cache, make forked chain creation await initialization, prevent stale throttled persistence writes after removal, and improve receipt/log index hygiene.
../../fix-report.md:280:**Issue:** The fork boundary check compared only the caller-provided hash against the internal fork hash, so an RPC hash alias could bypass it.
../../fix-report.md:281:**Fix:** Reject deletion after resolving the block whenever the resolved block object is the forked block.
../../fix-report.md:292:**Issue:** `createChain` returned a decorated chain before fork RPC bootstrap completed.
../../fix-report.md:302:**Location:** packages/receipt-manager/src/ReceiptManager.ts:471
../../fix-report.md:303:**Files modified:** packages/receipt-manager/src/ReceiptManager.ts
../../fix-report.md:304:**Issue:** Deleting receipts removed transaction-hash indexes without checking whether the index still belonged to the deleted block.
../../fix-report.md:308:**Location:** packages/receipt-manager/src/ReceiptManager.ts:322
../../fix-report.md:309:**Files modified:** packages/receipt-manager/src/ReceiptManager.ts
